1
00:00:05,688 --> 00:00:10,584
Krishna considers His own, so much so

2
00:00:10,981 --> 00:00:15,151
that in devotional expression, they

3
00:00:15,151 --> 00:00:18,677
take a position superior to that of the Lord at times.

4
00:00:18,677 --> 00:00:21,860
[On the Shoulders of the Lord]

5
00:00:21,860 --> 00:00:25,557
It's revealed in the beginning of the Chaitanya Charitamritam,

6
00:00:26,387 --> 00:00:30,411
Krishna's speaking very candidly, and says

7
00:00:31,056 --> 00:00:35,887
if aishwarya-jnan, too much knowledge

8
00:00:36,287 --> 00:00:44,791
of the majestic aspect of divinity,

9
00:00:45,991 --> 00:00:56,021
overwhelms, eclipses, conceals some potential

10
00:00:56,873 --> 00:01:04,208
for loving expression, He's disappointed.

11
00:01:08,119 --> 00:01:12,868
Whereas He says His preference, stated preferences,

12
00:01:12,868 --> 00:01:17,436
"But when my friends..." He's going above shanta-das, the friends,

13
00:01:17,436 --> 00:01:22,864
there's also shanta in Goloka, that's another thing we can discuss.

14
00:01:22,864 --> 00:01:25,431
I once said to Guru Maharaj, then understanding something,

15
00:01:25,431 --> 00:01:28,306
"Oh, so, shanta-rasa of Goloka would be different than

16
00:01:28,306 --> 00:01:31,893
shanta-rasa of Vaikuntha." And he said "Of course."

17
00:01:33,784 --> 00:01:36,331
We'll say something about that in a minute.

18
00:01:36,331 --> 00:01:45,244
So, what I prefer, we can say, a servitor position.

19
00:01:46,228 --> 00:01:50,994
Garud, Vishnu, and sometimes Krishna.

20
00:01:50,994 --> 00:01:57,599
Garuda, the beautiful eagle-like servitor,

21
00:02:00,367 --> 00:02:05,124
carrier of Vishnu, the famous Garuda.

22
00:02:05,124 --> 00:02:10,127
He's on the Thai money also, you know that,

23
00:02:10,127 --> 00:02:12,597
if you look on Thai money on the back.

24
00:02:16,395 --> 00:02:21,386
Riding on the shoulders of Garuda is Vishnu, Krishna.

25
00:02:21,386 --> 00:02:23,898
It's a very beautiful image.

26
00:02:23,898 --> 00:02:30,091
Also Satyabhama... was it Satyabhama?

27
00:02:30,091 --> 00:02:34,203
No, no... Rukmini, with Krishna.

28
00:02:35,233 --> 00:02:38,082
Krishna gives the parijata flower,

29
00:02:38,082 --> 00:02:42,431
later, Satyabhama wants a tree.

30
00:02:43,108 --> 00:02:49,489
Anyway, so, how ecstatic Garuda is to

31
00:02:51,304 --> 00:02:56,782
feel the Lord on his shoulders, the touch

32
00:02:56,782 --> 00:03:00,037
of the lotus feet and the divine form of the Lord

33
00:03:00,037 --> 00:03:03,668
upon his shoulders and he's flying happily.

34
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:07,201
How sweet that is.

35
00:03:08,012 --> 00:03:12,965
It's worshipable, and wonderful, and extra-ordinary.

36
00:03:13,714 --> 00:03:20,058
But, Krishna says in the begining of Charitamritam,

37
00:03:20,534 --> 00:03:25,744
"When I'm playing with the cowherd boys, my friends,

38
00:03:26,036 --> 00:03:34,739
sometimes I'm defeated. And the punishment for the defeated

39
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:40,791
is to carry the opponent on your shoulders."

40
00:03:41,699 --> 00:03:46,168
He's revealing, "You don't know how much joy

41
00:03:46,168 --> 00:03:52,489
it brings to my heart to carry my devotee on my shoulders."

42
00:03:55,780 --> 00:04:00,114
Garuda's ecstatic, carrying the Lord on his shoulders,

43
00:04:00,468 --> 00:04:07,049
but Krishna, He's ecstatic carrying a devotee on His shoulders,

44
00:04:07,449 --> 00:04:10,080
at the defeat of His devotee.

45
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:15,313
ye prāyaśo 'jita jito 'py asi tais tri-lokyām (SB 10.14.3)

46
00:04:15,313 --> 00:04:21,273
Ajita. Ajita Krishna. He is unconquerable,

47
00:04:21,719 --> 00:04:25,382
but He's conquered by devotion.

48
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:29,178
śrī-kṛṣṇā karṣiṇī ca sā (BRS 1.1.17)

49
00:04:29,178 --> 00:04:33,676
Krishna, everyone is being irresistably drawn

50
00:04:33,676 --> 00:04:41,024
in attraction to Krishna, and offering themselves in His service.

51
00:04:41,024 --> 00:04:44,583
But Krishna is being irresistably drawn

52
00:04:44,583 --> 00:04:48,092
to the devotion in the heart of the devotee,

53
00:04:48,092 --> 00:04:50,934
and wanting to serve them.

54
00:04:52,611 --> 00:04:58,894
That's the magic, the miracle, of Krishna consciousness.

55
00:04:59,479 --> 00:05:01,298
And then He goes further to say "You don't know

56
00:05:01,298 --> 00:05:04,485
how happy I am when the devotee is riding on my shoulders,

57
00:05:04,485 --> 00:05:09,619
then I am flying, like Garuda I'm flying

58
00:05:09,619 --> 00:05:12,273
with the devotee on my shoulder, I'm so happy."

59
00:05:13,949 --> 00:05:17,511
How can they climb on the shoulders of the Lord

60
00:05:17,511 --> 00:05:20,226
if it is not seva?

